    "To this end, we devised a methodology to evaluate the pipeline's performance using binary response questions (\"yes\" or \"no\"), enabling a rigorous assessment of the responses generated by the LLM (RAG-based LLM and LLaMA).",
    "Accuracy measures the percentage of exact predictions made by the LLM in addressing such inquiries out of the total number of expected answers.",
    "We designate answers provided by the framework that align with positive expected responses as true positives (TP), and those matching negative expected responses as true negatives (TN).",
    "Conversely, false positives (FP) occur when the pipeline yields positive responses contrary to the negative expected ones, while false negatives (FN) arise from the framework providing negative responses despite positive expectations.",
    "Thus, we defined accuracy as follows:Accuracy = T P + T N T P + F P + T N + F N (1)RQ2 evaluates the effects of employing various chunking techniques within the BPLLM pipeline, alongside investigating how prompt engineering can further augment the performance of the framework."
